summary:
Building Information Modeling (BIM) defined as:
 &ldquo;A digital representation of physical and functional characteristics of a facility. A BIM is a shared knowledge resource for information about a facility forming a reliable basis for decisions during its life-cycle; defined as existing from earliest conception to demolition.&ldquo;
 Course Information:          Course Title: CE-118L Building Information Modelling (BIM) Lab   Course Instructor: Engr.
